main event: A UFO report detailing misidentified objects observed flying in the Willamette Valley and Eastern Washington & Oregon in 1948.
interesting points: The reporting officer witnessed phenomena that could resemble flying disks during flights as a passenger., Reflections of the sun from metal roofs or buildings created illusions of airborne objects., The visibility conditions caused by haze contributed to the misidentifications., Acknowledgment that this report does not dismiss the possibility of actual flying disks., The report emphasizes the need for careful evaluation of similar future reports.
witness description: Commander W. J. Young, USNR, who has considerable flight experience.
